export const DAISYSP_REFERENCE = "# DaisySP DSP Primitive Reference\n\nMachine-readable reference extracted from DaisySP header files.\nSource: `/tmp/DaisySP/Source/` \u2014 all subdirectories.\n\n---\n\n## Synthesis\n\n### Oscillator \u2014 `Synthesis/oscillator.h`\nMulti-waveform oscillator with polyBLEP bandlimited variants.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process()\nSetFreq(float f)           // frequency Hz\nSetAmp(float a)            // amplitude\nSetWaveform(uint8_t wf)    // see enum below\nSetPw(float pw)            // pulse width 0-1 (square waves only)\nPhaseAdd(float _phase)     // add 0-1 to phase (for PM/FM)\nReset(float _phase = 0.0f)\nbool IsEOR() / IsEOC() / IsRising() / IsFalling()\n```\n**Waveforms:** `WAVE_SIN`, `WAVE_TRI`, `WAVE_SAW`, `WAVE_RAMP`, `WAVE_SQUARE`, `WAVE_POLYBLEP_TRI`, `WAVE_POLYBLEP_SAW`, `WAVE_POLYBLEP_SQUARE`, `WAVE_LAST`\n\n### Fm2 \u2014 `Synthesis/fm2.h`\nSimple 2-operator FM synth voice.\n```\nInit(float samplerate)\nfloat Process()\nSetFrequency(float freq)   // carrier freq Hz\nSetRatio(float ratio)      // mod/carrier ratio\nSetIndex(float index)      // FM depth (5 = 2PI rads)\nfloat GetIndex()\nvoid Reset()\n```\n\n### FormantOscillator \u2014 `Synthesis/formantosc.h`\nSinewave with aliasing-free phase reset (formant synthesis).\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process()\nSetFormantFreq(float freq)  // formant freq Hz\nSetCarrierFreq(float freq)  // carrier freq Hz\nSetPhaseShift(float ps)     // 0-1, negative ok\n```\n\n### HarmonicOscillator\\<N=16\\> \u2014 `Synthesis/harmonic_osc.h`\nChebyshev polynomial harmonic oscillator. Template: N = number of harmonics.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process()\nSetFreq(float freq)\nSetFirstHarmIdx(int idx)                // offset harmonic set (min 1)\nSetAmplitudes(const float* amplitudes)  // array of N floats, sum < 1\nSetSingleAmp(float amp, int idx)        // set one harmonic\n```\n\n### OscillatorBank \u2014 `Synthesis/oscillatorbank.h`\n7-voice divide-down organ (saw+square at 8'/4'/2'/1').\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process()\nSetFreq(float freq)\nSetAmplitudes(const float* amplitudes)  // 7 floats, sum = 1\nSetSingleAmp(float amp, int idx)        // idx 0-6\nSetGain(float gain)                     // 0-1\n```\n**Indices:** [0]=Saw8', [1]=Square8', [2]=Saw4', [3]=Square4', [4]=Saw2', [5]=Square2', [6]=Saw1'\n\n### VariableSawOscillator \u2014 `Synthesis/variablesawosc.h`\nSaw with variable slope or notch.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process()\nSetFreq(float frequency)\nSetPW(float pw)              // -1 to 1\nSetWaveshape(float waveshape) // 0=notch, 1=slope\n```\n\n### VariableShapeOscillator \u2014 `Synthesis/variableshapeosc.h`\nContinuously variable waveform + hard sync.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process()\nSetFreq(float frequency)\nSetPW(float pw)\nSetWaveshape(float waveshape)    // 0=saw/ramp/tri, 1=square\nSetSync(bool enable_sync)\nSetSyncFreq(float frequency)    // sync osc freq Hz\n```\n\n### VosimOscillator \u2014 `Synthesis/vosim.h`\nVOSIM: two sinewaves multiplied by and synced to a carrier.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process()\nSetFreq(float freq)         // carrier Hz\nSetForm1Freq(float freq)    // formant 1 Hz\nSetForm2Freq(float freq)    // formant 2 Hz\nSetShape(float shape)       // -1 to 1\n```\n\n### ZOscillator \u2014 `Synthesis/zoscillator.h`\nSine multiplied by and synced to a carrier with phase/offset control.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process()\nSetFreq(float freq)\nSetFormantFreq(float freq)\nSetShape(float shape)    // 0-1\nSetMode(float mode)      // -1 to 1; <1/3=phase shift, >2/3=offset, between=both\n```\n\n---\n\n## Filters\n\n### Svf \u2014 `Filters/svf.h`\nDouble-sampled stable State Variable Filter. 5 simultaneous outputs.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nvoid Process(float in)    // updates all outputs\nSetFreq(float f)          // cutoff Hz; 0 to sample_rate/3\nSetRes(float r)           // resonance 0-1\nSetDrive(float d)         // drive amount\nfloat Low() / High() / Band() / Notch() / Peak()\n```\n\n### LadderFilter \u2014 `Filters/ladder.h`\n4-pole Moog ladder (Huovilainen New Moog Model). 4x oversampled.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(float in)\nvoid ProcessBlock(float* buf, size_t size)\nSetFreq(float freq)            // cutoff Hz\nSetRes(float res)              // 0-1.8; self-oscillates high\nSetPassbandGain(float pbg)     // 0-0.5\nSetInputDrive(float drv)       // 0-4.0\nSetFilterMode(FilterMode mode) // see enum\n```\n**FilterMode:** `LP24`, `LP12`, `BP24`, `BP12`, `HP24`, `HP12`\n\n### OnePole \u2014 `Filters/onepole.h`\nLightweight 1-pole LP/HP. No sample_rate in Init.\n```\nvoid Init()\nfloat Process(float in)\nvoid ProcessBlock(float* in_out, size_t size)\nSetFrequency(float freq)       // normalized 0-0.497 (not Hz!)\nSetFilterMode(FilterMode mode) // FILTER_MODE_LOW_PASS or FILTER_MODE_HIGH_PASS\nvoid Reset()\n```\n\n### Soap \u2014 `Filters/soap.h`\nSecond-order allpass (bandpass + bandreject outputs).\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nvoid Process(float in)\nSetCenterFreq(float f)\nSetFilterBandwidth(float b)\nfloat Bandpass() / Bandreject()\n```\n\n### FIR\\<max_size, max_block\\> \u2014 `Filters/fir.h`\nTemplate FIR filter. ARM CMSIS-DSP optimized on ARM.\n```\nbool Init(const float* ir, size_t len, bool reverse)   // alias for SetIR\nfloat Process(float in)\nvoid ProcessBlock(const float* pSrc, float* pDst, size_t block)\nbool SetIR(const float* ir, size_t len, bool reverse)\nvoid Reset()\n```\n**Memory:** Internal mode: `state_[max_size + max_block - 1]` + `coefs_[max_size]` floats.\nUse `FIRFILTER_USER_MEMORY` (expands to `0, 0`) for external buffer mode.\n\n---\n\n## Effects\n\n### Chorus \u2014 `Effects/chorus.h`\nStereo chorus (two ChorusEngine instances).\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(float in)        // returns left\nfloat GetLeft() / GetRight()\nSetPan(float panl, float panr) / SetPan(float pan)\nSetLfoDepth(float depthl, float depthr) / SetLfoDepth(float depth)\nSetLfoFreq(float freql, float freqr) / SetLfoFreq(float freq)\nSetDelay(float delayl, float delayr) / SetDelay(float delay)     // 0-1\nSetDelayMs(float msl, float msr) / SetDelayMs(float ms)          // 0-50ms\nSetFeedback(float fbl, float fbr) / SetFeedback(float fb)        // 0-1\n```\n**Memory:** 2x `DelayLine<float, 2400>` (~19 KB)\n\n### Flanger \u2014 `Effects/flanger.h`\nFlanging effect with LFO-modulated delay.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(float in)\nSetFeedback(float feedback)   // 0-1\nSetLfoDepth(float depth)      // 0-1\nSetLfoFreq(float freq)        // Hz\nSetDelay(float delay)         // 0-1 (maps to 0.1-7ms)\nSetDelayMs(float ms)          // 0.1-7ms\n```\n**Memory:** `DelayLine<float, 960>` (~4 KB)\n\n### Phaser \u2014 `Effects/phaser.h`\nMulti-pole allpass phaser (up to 8 stages).\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(float in)\nSetPoles(int poles)          // 1-8\nSetLfoDepth(float depth)    // 0-1\nSetLfoFreq(float lfo_freq)  // Hz\nSetFreq(float ap_freq)      // allpass freq Hz\nSetFeedback(float feedback)  // 0-1\n```\n**Memory:** 8x `DelayLine<float, 2400>` (~75 KB). Use only needed poles.\n\n### PitchShifter \u2014 `Effects/pitchshifter.h`\nTime-domain pitch shifter with two crossfading delay lines.\n```\nInit(float sr)\nfloat Process(float &in)              // note: reference param\nSetTransposition(const float &transpose) // semitones (+/-)\nSetDelSize(uint32_t size)             // max 16384\nSetFun(float f)                       // flutter/randomness 0-1\n```\n**Memory:** 2x `DelayLine<float, 16384>` (~128 KB). `#define SHIFT_BUFFER_SIZE 16384`\n\n### Overdrive \u2014 `Effects/overdrive.h`\nDistortion module (tanh-based from Mutable Instruments).\n```\nvoid Init()\nfloat Process(float in)\nSetDrive(float drive)  // 0-1\n```\n\n### Decimator \u2014 `Effects/decimator.h`\nDownsampling + bitcrushing.\n```\nvoid Init()\nfloat Process(float input)\nSetDownsampleFactor(float downsample_factor)\nSetBitcrushFactor(float bitcrush_factor)     // 0-1\nSetBitsToCrush(const uint8_t &bits)          // 0-16\nSetSmoothCrushing(bool smooth_crushing)\n```\n\n### SampleRateReducer \u2014 `Effects/sampleratereducer.h`\nSample rate reduction.\n```\nvoid Init()\nfloat Process(float in)\nSetFreq(float frequency)  // 0-1 normalized (1=full quality)\n```\n\n### Wavefolder \u2014 `Effects/wavefolder.h`\nWavefolding (magnitudes > 1.0 fold back).\n```\nvoid Init()\nfloat Process(float in)\nSetGain(float gain)      // supports negative (thru-zero folding)\nSetOffset(float offset)  // pre-gain offset for asymmetry\n```\n\n### Tremolo \u2014 `Effects/tremolo.h`\nAmplitude modulation tremolo.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(float in)\nSetFreq(float freq)          // LFO rate Hz\nSetWaveform(int waveform)    // Oscillator::WAVE_* enum\nSetDepth(float depth)        // 0-1\n```\n\n### Autowah \u2014 `Effects/autowah.h`\nEnvelope-following wah.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(float in)\nSetWah(float wah)          // 0-1\nSetDryWet(float drywet)    // 0-100\nSetLevel(float level)      // 0-1\n```\n\n---\n\n## Drums\n\n### AnalogBassDrum \u2014 `Drums/analogbassdrum.h`\n808 bass drum model (revisited).\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(bool trigger = false)\nvoid Trig()\nSetSustain(bool sustain)\nSetAccent(float accent)              // 0-1\nSetFreq(float f0)                    // Hz\nSetTone(float tone)                  // click amount 0-1\nSetDecay(float decay)                // 0-1\nSetAttackFmAmount(float amount)      // 0-1\nSetSelfFmAmount(float amount)        // 0-1\n```\n\n### AnalogSnareDrum \u2014 `Drums/analogsnaredrum.h`\n808 snare drum model (revisited). 5 resonant modes.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(bool trigger = false)\nvoid Trig()\nSetSustain(bool sustain)\nSetAccent(float accent)    // 0-1\nSetFreq(float f0)          // Hz\nSetTone(float tone)        // brightness 0-1\nSetDecay(float decay)      // positive numbers\nSetSnappy(float snappy)    // 0=drum only, 1=snare only\n```\n\n### SyntheticBassDrum \u2014 `Drums/synthbassdrum.h`\nModulated oscillator bass drum (909-ish).\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(bool trigger = false)\nvoid Trig()\nSetSustain(bool sustain)\nSetAccent(float accent)                  // 0-1\nSetFreq(float freq)                      // Hz\nSetTone(float tone)                      // 0-1\nSetDecay(float decay)                    // 0-1\nSetDirtiness(float dirtiness)            // 0-1\nSetFmEnvelopeAmount(float amount)        // pitch sweep 0-1\nSetFmEnvelopeDecay(float decay)          // sweep duration 0-1\n```\n\n### SyntheticSnareDrum \u2014 `Drums/synthsnaredrum.h`\nModulated oscillator snare drum (909-ish). Mode ratio 1.47.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(bool trigger = false)\nvoid Trig()\nSetSustain(bool sustain)\nSetAccent(float accent)       // 0-1\nSetFreq(float f0)             // Hz\nSetFmAmount(float fm_amount)  // 0-1\nSetDecay(float decay)         // positive\nSetSnappy(float snappy)       // 0=drum, 1=snare\n```\n\n### HiHat\\<MetallicNoiseSource, VCA, resonance\\> \u2014 `Drums/hihat.h`\n808 hihat / cymbal. Template: noise source (SquareNoise/RingModNoise), VCA type, resonance toggle.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(bool trigger = false)\nvoid Trig()\nSetSustain(bool sustain)\nSetAccent(float accent)        // 0-1\nSetFreq(float f0)              // Hz\nSetTone(float tone)            // brightness 0-1\nSetDecay(float decay)          // 0-1 (internal: decay*1.7-1.2)\nSetNoisiness(float noisiness)  // 0=tone, 1=noise\n```\n**Default template:** `HiHat<SquareNoise, LinearVCA, true>`\n\n---\n\n## Physical Modeling\n\n### String \u2014 `PhysicalModeling/KarplusString.h`\nKarplus-Strong comb filter string (lite Rings implementation).\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(const float in)   // excitation input\nvoid Reset()\nSetFreq(float freq)\nSetNonLinearity(float amount)   // -1 to 0 = curved bridge, 0 to 1 = dispersion\nSetBrightness(float brightness) // 0-1\nSetDamping(float damping)       // 0-1\n```\n**Memory:** `DelayLine<float, 1024>` + `DelayLine<float, 256>` (~5 KB)\n\n### StringVoice \u2014 `PhysicalModeling/stringvoice.h`\nExtended Karplus-Strong with exciter (from Rings). Self-contained voice with trigger.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(bool trigger = false)\nvoid Trig()\nvoid Reset()\nSetSustain(bool sustain)        // continuous noise excitation\nSetFreq(float freq)\nSetAccent(float accent)         // 0-1\nSetStructure(float structure)   // 0-0.26=curved bridge, 0.26-1=dispersion\nSetBrightness(float brightness) // 0-1\nSetDamping(float damping)       // 0-1\nfloat GetAux()                  // raw excitation signal\n```\n**Memory:** ~5 KB (internal String instance)\n\n### ModalVoice \u2014 `PhysicalModeling/modalvoice.h`\nModal synthesis: click/noise \u2192 LPF \u2192 resonator. Self-contained voice.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(bool trigger = false)\nvoid Trig()\nSetSustain(bool sustain)          // continuous noise excitation\nSetFreq(float freq)               // resonator root Hz\nSetAccent(float accent)           // 0-1\nSetStructure(float structure)     // stiffness/brightness 0-1\nSetBrightness(float brightness)   // 0-1\nSetDamping(float damping)         // decay time 0-1\nfloat GetAux()                    // raw excitation signal\n```\n\n### Resonator \u2014 `PhysicalModeling/resonator.h`\nResonant body simulation. Up to 24 modes in batches of 4.\n```\nInit(float position, int resolution, float sample_rate)\n    // position: amplitude phase offset 0-1\n    // resolution: quality vs speed\nfloat Process(const float in)\nSetFreq(float freq)\nSetStructure(float structure)     // 0-1\nSetBrightness(float brightness)   // 0-1\nSetDamping(float damping)         // 0-1\n```\n**Constants:** `kMaxNumModes = 24`, `kModeBatchSize = 4`\n\n### Drip \u2014 `PhysicalModeling/drip.h`\nWater drip physical model (Perry Cook).\n```\nInit(float sample_rate, float dettack)  // dettack = stop period\nfloat Process(bool trig)\n```\nNo public setters \u2014 parameters set at Init.\n\n---\n\n## Noise\n\n### WhiteNoise \u2014 `Noise/whitenoise.h`\nFast white noise (linear congruential generator).\n```\nvoid Init()            // no sample_rate\nfloat Process()        // returns -amp to +amp\nSetAmp(float a)\nSetSeed(int32_t s)     // 0 corrected to 1\n```\n\n### Dust \u2014 `Noise/dust.h`\nSparse random impulses.\n```\nvoid Init()            // calls SetDensity(0.5f)\nfloat Process()        // returns random value or 0\nSetDensity(float density)  // 0-1\n```\n\n### ClockedNoise \u2014 `Noise/clockednoise.h`\nSample-and-hold noise at target frequency.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process()\nSetFreq(float freq)    // Hz\nvoid Sync()            // force new sample\n```\n\n### GrainletOscillator \u2014 `Noise/grainlet.h`\nGranular oscillator: phase-distorted sine \u00d7 continuous sine synced to carrier.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process()\nSetFreq(float freq)          // carrier Hz\nSetFormantFreq(float freq)   // formant Hz\nSetShape(float shape)        // 0-1, 1-2, >2 behave differently\nSetBleed(float bleed)        // 0-1\n```\n\n### Particle \u2014 `Noise/particle.h`\nRandom impulse train \u2192 resonant SVF filter.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process()\nfloat GetNoise()              // raw pre-filter noise\nSetFreq(float frequency)     // filter center Hz\nSetResonance(float resonance) // 0-1\nSetRandomFreq(float freq)    // randomization rate Hz\nSetDensity(float density)    // 0-1\nSetGain(float gain)          // 0-1\nSetSpread(float spread)      // freq randomization amount\nSetSync(bool sync)           // force re-randomize\n```\n\n### FractalRandomGenerator\\<T, order\\> \u2014 `Noise/fractal_noise.h`\nStacked octaves of a noise source T (must have Init/SetFreq).\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process()\nSetFreq(float freq)    // lowest octave Hz\nSetColor(float color)  // 0=dark, 1=bright\n```\n\n---\n\n## Control\n\n### Adsr \u2014 `Control/adsr.h`\nClassic ADSR envelope.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate, int blockSize = 1)\nfloat Process(bool gate)\nSetTime(int seg, float time)                        // seconds per segment\nSetAttackTime(float timeInS, float shape = 0.0f)    // attack + optional shape\nSetDecayTime(float timeInS)\nSetReleaseTime(float timeInS)\nSetSustainLevel(float sus_level)                     // 0-1\nvoid Retrigger(bool hard)     // hard=true clicks\nuint8_t GetCurrentSegment()\nbool IsRunning()\n```\n**Segments:** `ADSR_SEG_IDLE=0`, `ADSR_SEG_ATTACK=1`, `ADSR_SEG_DECAY=2`, `ADSR_SEG_RELEASE=4`\n\n### AdEnv \u2014 `Control/adenv.h`\nTrigger-able AD (attack-decay) envelope.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process()\nvoid Trigger()\nSetTime(uint8_t seg, float time)  // ADENV_SEG_ATTACK or ADENV_SEG_DECAY, seconds\nSetCurve(float scalar)            // positive=log; -100 to 100+\nSetMin(float min)\nSetMax(float max)\nfloat GetValue()\nuint8_t GetCurrentSegment()\nbool IsRunning()\n```\n**Segments:** `ADENV_SEG_IDLE`, `ADENV_SEG_ATTACK`, `ADENV_SEG_DECAY`, `ADENV_SEG_LAST`\n\n### Phasor \u2014 `Control/phasor.h`\nNormalized 0-to-1 ramp at specified frequency.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate, float freq, float initial_phase)\nInit(float sample_rate, float freq)\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process()        // returns 0-1\nSetFreq(float freq)    // Hz\nfloat GetFreq()\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dynamics\n\n### CrossFade \u2014 `Dynamics/crossfade.h`\nCrossfade between two signals with selectable curve.\n```\nInit(int curve) / Init()    // default CROSSFADE_LIN\nfloat Process(float &in1, float &in2)\nSetPos(float pos)           // 0-1\nSetCurve(uint8_t curve)\n```\n**Curves:** `CROSSFADE_LIN`, `CROSSFADE_CPOW`, `CROSSFADE_LOG`, `CROSSFADE_EXP`\n\n### Limiter \u2014 `Dynamics/limiter.h`\nSimple peak limiter.\n```\nvoid Init()\nvoid ProcessBlock(float *in, size_t size, float pre_gain)  // in-place\n```\nNo setters.\n\n---\n\n## Utility\n\n### DelayLine\\<T, max_size\\> \u2014 `Utility/delayline.h`\nTemplated delay line with linear + Hermite interpolation.\n```\nvoid Init()  / void Reset()\nSetDelay(size_t delay)    // integer samples\nSetDelay(float delay)     // fractional samples\nvoid Write(const T sample)\nconst T Read()                      // at set delay (linear interp)\nconst T Read(float delay)           // at arbitrary offset\nconst T ReadHermite(float delay)    // Hermite cubic interp\nconst T Allpass(const T sample, size_t delay, const T coefficient)\n```\n**Memory:** `T line_[max_size]` embedded in object. For large delays use `DSY_SDRAM_BSS`.\n\n### DcBlock \u2014 `Utility/dcblock.h`\nDC offset removal.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(float in)\n```\n\n### Metro \u2014 `Utility/metro.h`\nClock/metronome trigger generator.\n```\nInit(float freq, float sample_rate)\nuint8_t Process()    // returns 1 on tick, 0 otherwise\nSetFreq(float freq)  // Hz\nvoid Reset()\n```\n\n### Maytrig \u2014 `Utility/maytrig.h`\nProbabilistic trigger (coin flip per call).\n```\n// No Init needed\nfloat Process(float prob)  // prob 0-1; returns 1.0 or 0.0\n```\n\n### SampleHold \u2014 `Utility/samplehold.h`\nSample-and-hold / track-and-hold.\n```\n// No Init needed\nfloat Process(bool trigger, float input, Mode mode = MODE_SAMPLE_HOLD)\n```\n**Modes:** `MODE_SAMPLE_HOLD`, `MODE_TRACK_HOLD`\n\n### SmoothRandomGenerator \u2014 `Utility/smooth_random.h`\nSmoothstep-interpolated random values at target rate.\n```\nInit(float sample_rate)\nfloat Process()        // -1 to 1\nSetFreq(float freq)    // Hz\n```\n\n### Looper \u2014 `Utility/looper.h`\nMultimode audio looper. Caller provides buffer.\n```\nInit(float *mem, size_t size)    // external buffer\nfloat Process(const float input)\nvoid TrigRecord()        // toggle record\nvoid Clear()\nSetMode(Mode mode)\nvoid IncrementMode()\nvoid ToggleReverse() / SetReverse(bool state)\nvoid ToggleHalfSpeed() / SetHalfSpeed(bool state)\nSetIncrementSize(float increment)\nbool Recording() / RecordingQueued()\nMode GetMode()\n```\n**Modes:** `NORMAL`, `ONETIME_DUB`, `REPLACE`, `FRIPPERTRONICS` (decay \u2248 0.707)\n\n---\n\n## Sampling\n\n### GranularPlayer \u2014 `Sampling/granularplayer.h`\nGranular sample player with independent time stretch and pitch shift.\n```\nInit(float* sample, int size, float sample_rate)\nfloat Process(float speed, float transposition, float grain_size)\n    // speed: multiplier (1=normal, negative=reverse)\n    // transposition: cents (100 = 1 semitone)\n    // grain_size: milliseconds (min 1)\n```\n**Memory:** Caller provides sample buffer. Internal `float cosEnv_[256]` (1 KB).\n\n---\n\n## Memory & Platform Notes\n\n### SDRAM Usage\nLarge buffers must use `DSY_SDRAM_BSS` attribute to place in external SDRAM (64 MB on Daisy Patch):\n```cpp\n// Global scope \u2014 SDRAM\nstatic DelayLine<float, 48000> DSY_SDRAM_BSS my_delay;  // ~192 KB\nstatic float DSY_SDRAM_BSS looper_buf[48000 * 60];      // ~11.5 MB\n```\n\n### DTCMRAM vs SDRAM\n- **DTCMRAM** (128 KB): fast, zero-wait-state. Stack + small globals live here by default.\n- **SRAM** (512 KB): main RAM. Default for `.bss` and `.data`.\n- **SDRAM** (64 MB): external, slower. Use `DSY_SDRAM_BSS` for large audio buffers.\n\n### Stack Limits\n- Default stack: ~8 KB (configurable in linker script)\n- Do NOT allocate large arrays on stack \u2014 use static globals or SDRAM\n- DelayLine internally stores `T line_[max_size]` \u2014 must be static/global for large sizes\n\n### DelayLine Declaration Patterns\n```cpp\n// Small (fits in SRAM): static global\nstatic DelayLine<float, 960> flanger_delay;\n\n// Medium (fits in SRAM, but watch total): static global\nstatic DelayLine<float, 4800> chorus_delay;\n\n// Large (needs SDRAM):\nstatic DelayLine<float, 48000> DSY_SDRAM_BSS reverb_delay;\n\n// Very large (always SDRAM):\nstatic DelayLine<float, 96000> DSY_SDRAM_BSS long_delay;\n```\n\n### AudioCallback Safety\n- `Process()` calls happen inside the audio interrupt \u2014 keep them fast\n- No heap allocation (`new`, `malloc`) in audio callback\n- No STL containers or `std::string`\n- No `printf` / logging\n- All DSP objects must be initialized in `main()` before `StartAudio()`\n- Use `static` globals for all DSP state\n\n### Common Utility Functions (`Utility/dsp.h`)\n```cpp\nfloat mtof(float m)           // MIDI note \u2192 frequency\nfloat fclamp(float in, float min, float max)\nfloat fmap(float in, float min, float max, Mapping curve)  // LINEAR, EXP, LOG\nfloat SoftClip(float x)       // -3..3 input\nfloat SoftLimit(float x)\nvoid fonepole(float &out, float in, float coeff)  // one-pole LPF\nvoid TestFloat(float &x, float y = 0.f)           // NaN/Inf guard\n```\n**Constants:** `PI_F`, `TWOPI_F`, `HALFPI_F`, `kOneTwelfth` (for `pow(2, kOneTwelfth * semitones)`)\n";
